  "prompt": "Is it the norm to put your degrees in your email signature?",
  "response": "Including degrees in your email signature can vary depending on the context and personal preference. In professional settings, particularly in academia, healthcare, or certain scientific fields, it is more common to include credentials (like PhDs, MDs, etc.) to establish qualifications. In more casual or corporate environments, it may be less common or unnecessary.\n\nIf you choose to include your degrees, you might do so to convey expertise or enhance your professional image. It is typically best to keep your signature concise and relevant to your audience. Ultimately, the decision should align with your professional identity and the conventions of your industry.",
